<node CREATED="1289232124561" ID="ID_865136363" MODIFIED="1289232128169" TEXT="Facebook Connect">
<node CREATED="1289234606652" ID="ID_1094143564" MODIFIED="1289234608589" TEXT="Resources">
<node CREATED="1289234619854" ID="ID_311278785" LINK="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Facebook_Beacon" MODIFIED="1289234624270" TEXT="Facebook Beacon - Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia"/>
<node CREATED="1289234685520" ID="ID_556545498" LINK="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Facebook_Platform#Facebook_Connect" MODIFIED="1289234698473" TEXT="Facebook Connect - Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia"/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1289234599814" ID="ID_205998048" MODIFIED="1289234601295" TEXT="Overview">
<node CREATED="1289234601911" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_382109068" MODIFIED="1289234721948" TEXT="Facebook Connect was launched in December 2008.">
<node CREATED="1289234722557" ID="ID_346918946" MODIFIED="1289234722557" TEXT="At the time, Facebook was a walled garden&#x2014;all content stayed within the site. MySpace, Google, and other networks were lining up to use the OpenSocial platform to allow applications to be built once and run on multiple platforms."/>
<node CREATED="1289234715444" ID="ID_1634775075" MODIFIED="1289234749120" TEXT="Facebook then launched Beacon to allow external sites that users visited to post Facebook status updates on the users&#x2019; behalf."/>
<node CREATED="1289234749406" ID="ID_479648806" MODIFIED="1289234771625" TEXT="Unfortunately, Beacon had public-relations(&#x516c;&#x5171;&#x95dc;&#x4fc2;) issues. The default setting for publishing updates was on, and users did not like having everyone know what they were doing without their permission."/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1289234806154" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_902700776" MODIFIED="1289234812542" TEXT="Facebook Connect went in a different direction. Users explicitly use Connect to log in to external sites using their Facebook credentials.">
<node CREATED="1289234814253" ID="ID_1447956505" MODIFIED="1289234842173" TEXT="These websites then become more valuable to them because they have the ability to incorporate information from their Facebook friends."/>
<node CREATED="1289234842407" ID="ID_1868433666" MODIFIED="1289234842777" TEXT="Currently, more than 15,000 websites have implemented Facebook Connect into their sites. Many of these sites have seen a massive increase in registrations, engagement, and &apos;&apos;friend referrals&apos;&apos;."/>
</node>
</node>
</node>
